Anchor CoinStats wallet balance to holdings value during quota gaps.

When the CoinStats free-tier credit limit is reached, every wallet endpoint
returns 406 and the account snapshot yields a zero balance. Sure's reverse-
balance materializer then sets cash = -holdings, collapsing the account to $0
even though the (preserved) holdings still carry their last-good qty x price.

Single-asset wallet holdings are NOT deleted during a gap: process_single_asset
_holding early-returns on zero quantity without calling cleanup_stale_holdings!
(only the exchange-portfolio path prunes). So their value is a safe fallback:
when CoinStats supplies no balance, anchor the account to the sum of its latest
holdings instead of zero, and treat cash as zero (a bare wallet holds no cash).

Optional patch (off by default); enabled per-deployment via patchFlags.
diff --git a/app/models/coinstats_account/processor.rb b/app/models/coinstats_account/processor.rb
index c607163..f3ccdaa 100644
--- a/app/models/coinstats_account/processor.rb
+++ b/app/models/coinstats_account/processor.rb
@@ -52,6 +52,21 @@ class CoinstatsAccount::Processor
       currency = parse_currency(coinstats_account.currency) || account.currency || "USD"
       cash_balance = coinstats_account.inferred_cash_balance
 
+      # Quota-gap resilience: when CoinStats returns no usable balance (e.g. the
+      # free-tier credit limit is reached and wallet endpoints 406), the snapshot
+      # yields a zero anchor, which the reverse-balance materializer turns into
+      # cash = -holdings, collapsing the account to $0 despite valued holdings.
+      # Single-asset wallet holdings are preserved during a gap, so fall back to
+      # their value rather than zeroing crypto we still have a last-good price for.
+      if balance.to_d.zero?
+        latest_holding_date = account.holdings.maximum(:date)
+        holdings_value = latest_holding_date ? account.holdings.where(date: latest_holding_date).sum(:amount) : 0.to_d
+        if holdings_value.to_d.positive?
+          balance = holdings_value
+          cash_balance = 0.to_d
+        end
+      end
+
       account.update!(
         balance: balance,
         cash_balance: cash_balance,
